<H3> <TI>   Local Structure Determination of </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Local Structure Determination of </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
BP   by X- Ray Spectroscopy 
[.sub]13[/][.sub]2[/] 
<F P=102> 43070061W Tokyo ISBB'93 in English Aug 93 p 104--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 43070061W </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ISBB'93 </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [English abstract of article by Kuniko Maeda and Tomoyuki </F>
Isomura, Institute of Physical and Chemical Research (RIKEN); 
and Jun Kuwai and Hirohiko Adachi, Department of Metallurgy, 
Kyoto University] 
  [Text] The crystal structure of 
B[.sub]13[/]P[.sub]2[/] has been determined to be the 
_a_-rhombohedral boron structure with two phosphorous atoms 
(partly replaced by boron) in a unit cell from X-ray 
diffraction.[.sup]1[/] We measured P 3p electron density of 
states (DOS) of B[.sub]13[/]P[.sub]2[/] by X-ray emission 
spectroscopy.[.sup]2[/] 
  We calculate the P 3p DOS of three structures of 
B[.sub]13[/]P[.sub]2[/]: (a) the two P sites are fully 
occupied by P, (b) one of the P sites is replaced by B and (c) 
one of the P sites is vacant. In Figure 1, the calculated DOS 
are compared with the measured P 3p DOS. It is found from Figure 
1 that the experiment remarkably agrees with model (c), but does 
not agree with model (a) nor (b). Consequently one of the P 
sites is vacant and is not replaced by B. We conclude that the 
structure of B[.sub]13[/]P[.sub]2[/] is that shown in 
Figure 2. 

